    "blocks": [
        {
            "id": "intro_conditionals",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Functions with Conditionals",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 1
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Functions become more powerful when you add conditionals. They can make decisions and return different results based on the input."
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "This lets you write flexible functions that handle different situations."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "basic_conditional",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Adding If Statements",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 2
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "You can use `if`, `elif`, and `else` inside functions just like anywhere else in Python."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def check_age(age):\n    if age >= 18:\n        print(\"Adult\")\n    else:\n        print(\"Minor\")\n\ncheck_age(20)\ncheck_age(15)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Adult\nMinor"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The function behaves differently based on the age value."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "returning_based_on_condition",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Instead of printing, you can **return** different values based on conditions. This is more useful because you can use the result in your code."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def get_grade(score):\n    if score >= 90:\n        return \"A\"\n    elif score >= 80:\n        return \"B\"\n    elif score >= 70:\n        return \"C\"\n    else:\n        return \"F\"\n\nresult = get_grade(85)\nprint(f\"Grade: {result}\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Grade: B"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The function returns different grades based on the score."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
