            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "early_return",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Remember that `return` exits the function immediately. You can use this for **early returns** to simplify logic."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def validate_age(age):\n    if age < 0:\n        return \"Invalid age\"\n    if age < 13:\n        return \"Child\"\n    if age < 18:\n        return \"Teen\"\n    return \"Adult\"\n\nprint(validate_age(15))",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Teen"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Once a condition matches, the function returns immediately and stops checking."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_early_return",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "What happens when a function hits a return statement?"
                },
                {
                    "type": "mcq",
                    "content": "",
                    "properties": {
                        "question": "",
                        "options": [
                            "It continues to the next line",
                            "It exits the function immediately",
                            "It waits for more code"
                        ],
                        "correctAnswerIndex": 1,
                        "correctFeedback": "Correct! return exits the function right away.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "return exits the function immediately, no more code runs.",
                        "explanation": "Once return executes, the function ends and returns the value."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "boolean_returns",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Returning Boolean Values",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 2
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Functions often return `True` or `False` to check conditions. These are called **predicate functions**."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def is_positive(num):\n    if num > 0:\n        return True\n    else:\n        return False\n\nif is_positive(5):\n    print(\"Positive number!\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Positive number!"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The function returns `True` or `False`, which can be used in conditions."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "simplified_boolean",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "You can simplify boolean returns by returning the condition directly."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "# Long way\ndef is_even(num):\n    if num % 2 == 0:\n        return True\n    else:\n        return False\n\n# Shorter way\ndef is_even(num):\n    return num % 2 == 0\n\nprint(is_even(4))",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "True"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Both do the same thing, but the second is simpler and clearer."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_boolean",
